                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Moscow, Dec. 7 (Agencies): India today signed a path-breaking civil nuclear agreement with Russia that will ensure transfer of technology and uninterrupted uranium fuel supplies.          
	The pact was clinched after talks between Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and Russian President Dmitry Medvedev at the Kremlin. The deal goes much further than the 123 Agreement with the US.                  
	 New Delhi: The dates for Bangladesh Prime Minister Sheikh Hasinas planned visit from December 19 are likely to be reworked because of Prime Minister Manmohan Singhs unscheduled trip to the global climate meet in Copenhagen. But the two are likely to meet on the conferences sidelines.                  
	 New Delhi: The Supreme Court on Monday directed all states to frame within four weeks policies to deal with unauthorised religious structures in public space, and retain or demolish them in accordance with the rules. The move is a follow-up to the courts September order banning such unauthorised structures on public land such as parks.                   
	 Mumbai: The special court hearing the 26/11 case has asked the prosecution to finish presenting evidence by December 9, the deadline signalling the start of final phase of the trial of Pakistani gunman Ajmal Kasab and two others.           The process , to be completed by November 26, was delayed because of the removal of Kasabs lawyer.                  
	 New Delhi: The Centre has decided to sign an understanding with Sri Lanka to ensure the safety of Tamil Nadu fishermen straying into the neighbours waters, external affairs minister S.M. Krishna told the Rajya Sabha on Monday. The move follows complaints the Lankan navy was cracking down on the fishermen entering the waters near Kachativu island by mistake.                                                                                                                                              
